      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIKI TO SUCCESS (10) kicked off his campaign with fourths at Group 1 level behind the likes of Leap To Fame and Swayzee and has won both starts since despite working. Covered ground and was hampered by a flat tyre but still managed to set a new track record in winning the Charlton Cup last start. Two from two at this distance. The one to beat. OLIVER DAN (7) draws wide but is capable on his day and is working towards a win having been beaten just over 5m into fourth in his last two outings. JILLIBY NITRO (5) found winning form in the Geelong Cup two back and was a solid fourth form the back line at Melton last start. Races well here with two wins and three placings in six attempts. ISTHISJUSTFANTASY (9) is a first four hope off her win two back at Melton.",
